return ['messages'=>['1476df57f1fd2fb57e7a2e9e7ec932e9'=>'Can\'t you imagine it?','189de84a1b3623ebd8fdd55a45d1ca84'=>'I have always thought that eroticism does not detract from the artistic value that a work may have. And I have held on to that thought, which is why I have sought to demonstrate it with my photography all these years. ','23f9176f75b20ff03dc0cff48343270e'=>'Need an example?','330165ccb6d8dd34c1f45c4a3cc262bc'=>'Anyway, you can agree with me or not, and either way it\'s wonderful. Differences of opinion are not bad, even though we often think they are. But whether you agree with what I say or not, I invite you to analyze it more deeply and try to look beyond it the next time you see an explicit, erotic or pornographic photograph, and ask yourself: What do I feel when I see this?  ','3aadd5c8dbb55e5d151b91a5a8f00933'=>'I don\'t know if you can see more or less of the person\'s body; there are extremely erotic photographs in which no one appears, you can simply see, for example, a wrinkled sheet, as if someone had just gotten up, and it invites you to think about what must have happened when that someone was in that bed.','3fb49f74da782c28370ef9860a0da9ee'=>'On the contrary, erotic art focuses on creating an atmosphere, immersing you in a world with its own air, its own light, full of smells, textures, flavors, stimuli that, although they are not “real,” you can perceive and your body receives them without realizing that small detail. You feel curious, maybe nostalgic, you get excited and experience feelings of closeness and intimacy. ','589e9bfb3071793b583108491b8d9e85'=>'Even today in the 21st century, we are not able to give a defined concept to art. We understand that this concept changes from one person to another, however we have certain aspects on which we tend to agree (not always), such as what is beautiful or aesthetic. But art is not limited to expressing what is beautiful, this has led us to understand that a work of art is one that makes you feel something, that generates an emotion. These can be emotions that we understand as positive or not; that is why there is “ugly” art, since it is associated with emotions that we are not used to feeling or we consider negative.   ','5ac7733269267859a406504937390e27'=>'Needless to say, I have nothing against porn, I think it is very necessary that there be all kinds of representation regarding sex. Furthermore, with feminist porn, the barrier between eroticism and porn is increasingly being broken down. ','7a1834fd92934057725a8f0f7fcf4182'=>'<em>It is visual poetry.</em>','8a31e90753cc35ccfba56fb26404c11f'=>'Porn is not only explicit, but it is often direct, obvious... Everything is too much on the table, and it doesn\'t leave us much room for our mind or our emotions to play. That\'s why porn doesn\'t make you feel more than a little warmth in your crotch; but on an emotional level, nothing. ','9ff57ed6369a8bcacdd7fdd7f2986aa3'=>'We then understand that “what is shown” is not the determining factor.','<em><mark style="background-color:#e0e0e0" class="has-inline-color has-black-color"><strong>(Si alguien conoce al autor de esta fotografía, estaría encantada de que me lo dijera</strong>).</mark></em>'=>'<em><mark style="background-color:#e0e0e0" class="has-inline-color has-black-color"><strong>(If anyone knows the author of this photograph, I would be delighted if you could tell me.)</strong></mark></em>','<em>Es poesía visual.</em>'=>'<em>It is visual poetry.</em>','Aún hoy en el siglo XXI, no somos capaces de dar un concepto definido al arte. Entendemos que dicho concepto cambia de una persona a otra, sin embargo tenemos ciertos aspectos en los que solemos estar de acuerdo (no siempre), como por ejemplo lo que es bello o estético. Pero el arte no se queda solo en expresar lo que es bello, eso nos ha llevado a entender, que una obra de arte es aquella que te hace sentir algo, que te genera una emoción. Pueden ser emociones que entendemos como positivas o no; es por eso que hay arte “feo”, ya que se asocia con las emociones que no estamos acostumbrados a sentir o consideramos negativas.'=>'Even today in the 21st century, we are not able to give a defined concept to art. We understand that this concept changes from one person to another, however we have certain aspects on which we tend to agree (not always), such as what is beautiful or aesthetic. But art is not limited to expressing what is beautiful, this has led us to understand that a work of art is one that makes you feel something, that generates an emotion. These can be emotions that we understand as positive or not; that is why there is “ugly” art, since it is associated with emotions that we are not used to feeling or we consider negative.   ','Con esto no pretendo decir que una cosa sea mejor que otra, son diferencias que con los años y tras muchos debates he ido estableciendo.'=>'With this I do not mean to say that one thing is better than another, these are differences that I have established over the years and after many debates.','Demás está decir que yo no tengo nada en contra del porno, me parece muy necesario que exista todo tipo de representación en cuanto al sexo. Además, con el porno feminista, cada vez se está rompiendo más esa barrera entre el erotismo y el porno.'=>'Needless to say, I have nothing against porn, I think it is very necessary that there be all kinds of representation regarding sex. Furthermore, with feminist porn, the barrier between eroticism and porn is increasingly being broken down. ','ESE, es el factor determinante. <strong><em>Lo que te hace sentir.</em></strong>'=>'THAT is the determining factor. <strong><em>What makes you feel.</em></strong>','El porno no solo es explícito, sino que suele ser directo, evidente… Todo está demasiado allí sobre la mesa, y no nos deja mucho espacio para que nuestra mente o nuestras emociones jueguen. Es por ello, que el porno no te hace sentir más que un calorcito en la entrepierna; pero a nivel emocional, nada.'=>'Porn is not only explicit, but it is often direct, obvious... Everything is too much on the table, and it doesn\'t leave us much room for our mind or our emotions to play. That\'s why porn doesn\'t make you feel more than a little warmth in your crotch; but on an emotional level, nothing. ','En fin, que puedes concordar conmigo o no, y de cualquier manera es maravilloso. Las diferencias de opiniones no son malas, a pesar de que muchas veces así lo pensamos. Pero estés o no de acuerdo con lo que digo, te invito a analizarlo con mayor profundidad y tratar de observar más allá la próxima vez que veas una fotografía explícita, erótica o pornográfica, y te preguntes: ¿Qué siento al ver esto?'=>'Anyway, you can agree with me or not, and either way it\'s wonderful. Differences of opinion are not bad, even though we often think they are. But whether you agree with what I say or not, I invite you to analyze it more deeply and try to look beyond it the next time you see an explicit, erotic or pornographic photograph, and ask yourself: What do I feel when I see this?  ','Entendemos entonces que “lo que se muestre” no es el factor determinante.'=>'We then understand that “what is shown” is not the determining factor.','Entonces, ¿qué es lo que, a mi parecer, hace que una fotografía pueda perder su potencial artístico?'=>'So what is it, in my opinion, that makes a photograph lose its artistic potential?','Es invitar, dejándote la decisión de entrar. No empujarte hacia la puerta y obligarte a quedarte.'=>'It\'s inviting, leaving you the decision to come in. Not pushing you out the door and forcing you to stay. ','Muy por el contrario, el arte erótico, se enfoca en crear una atmósfera, en sumergirte en un mundo con su propio aire, su propia luz, lleno de olores, texturas, sabores, estímulos que, aunque no sean “reales”, puedes percibirlos y tu cuerpo los recibe sin darse cuenta de ese pequeño detalle. Te sientes curioso, puede que nostálgico, te emocionas y experimentas sensaciones de cercanía e intimidad.'=>'On the contrary, erotic art focuses on creating an atmosphere, immersing you in a world with its own air, its own light, full of smells, textures, flavors, stimuli that, although they are not “real,” you can perceive and your body receives them without realizing that small detail. You feel curious, maybe nostalgic, you get excited and experience feelings of closeness and intimacy. ','No si se ve más o menos del cuerpo de las personas; hay fotografías sumamente eróticas en las que no aparece nadie, simplemente se ve, por ejemplo, una sábana arrugada, como si alguien acabara de levantarse, y te invita a pensar qué habrá pasado cuando ese alguien estuvo en esa cama.'=>'I don\'t know if you can see more or less of the person\'s body; there are extremely erotic photographs in which no one appears, you can simply see, for example, a wrinkled sheet, as if someone had just gotten up, and it invites you to think about what must have happened when that someone was in that bed.','Ojalá en un futuro no muy lejano, podamos ir al cine a ver pornografía que merezca la pena estar en las pantallas grandes.'=>'Hopefully in the not too distant future, we will be able to go to the cinema to watch pornography that is worthy of being on the big screen.','Si me van siguiendo, ya se habrán dado cuenta cuál es el factor principal que resta el potencial artístico de una obra erótica. Es básicamente, la diferencia entre erotismo y porno.'=>'If you\'ve been following me, you\'ll have already realized what the main factor is that reduces the artistic potential of an erotic work. It\'s basically the difference between eroticism and porn. ','Siempre he pensado que el erotismo no resta el valor artístico que pueda tener una obra. Y me he aferrado mucho a ese pensamiento, por eso he buscado demostrarlo con mi fotografía todos estos años.'=>'I have always thought that eroticism does not detract from the artistic value that a work may have. And I have held on to that thought, which is why I have sought to demonstrate it with my photography all these years. ','Siento que tengo bastante claro cuáles son los aspectos específicos que pueden hacer que una fotografía erótica pierda su valor artístico. Y no se trata necesariamente de lo explícita que ésta sea. Porque no importa cuán explícita sea una obra, si se trabaja desde una cierta perspectiva, con una intención clara, y se sabe jugar con la iluminación, puedes tener una imagen sumamente potente, erótica y que tenga todo el potencial para ser expuesta en galerías de arte.'=>'I feel that I have a pretty good idea of ​​what specific aspects can make an erotic photograph lose its artistic value. And it is not necessarily about how explicit it is. Because no matter how explicit a work is, if you work from a certain perspective, with a clear intention, and you know how to play with lighting, you can have an extremely powerful, erotic image that has all the potential to be exhibited in art galleries.  ','a68010012e71faf0517adb0bce389189'=>'With this I do not mean to say that one thing is better than another, these are differences that I have established over the years and after many debates.','b7c0375d012ac27dbb3731f510450759'=>'<em><mark style="background-color:#e0e0e0" class="has-inline-color has-black-color"><strong>(If anyone knows the author of this photograph, I would be delighted if you could tell me.)</strong></mark></em>','bb88e3ba57e323fb3d8f1da0e0fd3e5c'=>'It\'s inviting, leaving you the decision to come in. Not pushing you out the door and forcing you to stay. ','c0acb5019db69507584db5243bb53126'=>'Hopefully in the not too distant future, we will be able to go to the cinema to watch pornography that is worthy of being on the big screen.','c7203d3917c44c885c32f07c468ff8cc'=>'If you\'ve been following me, you\'ll have already realized what the main factor is that reduces the artistic potential of an erotic work. It\'s basically the difference between eroticism and porn. ','e9781560ce69e1845d5ec64bdabf0eb1'=>'So what is it, in my opinion, that makes a photograph lose its artistic potential?','f44f3a3bc4be9a0b2350f7e01c33e0b3'=>'I feel that I have a pretty good idea of ​​what specific aspects can make an erotic photograph lose its artistic value. And it is not necessarily about how explicit it is. Because no matter how explicit a work is, if you work from a certain perspective, with a clear intention, and you know how to play with lighting, you can have an extremely powerful, erotic image that has all the potential to be exhibited in art galleries.  ','fee796f41a47b0f246da0a37fa7c91b3'=>'THAT is the determining factor. <strong><em>What makes you feel.</em></strong>','¿Necesitas un ejemplo?'=>'Need an example?','¿No puedes imaginarlo?'=>'Can\'t you imagine it?']];
